THREE Glasgow accountants will race against the clock to complete four gruelling cycle stages for charity. Accountants add on miles for charity THREE Glasgow accountants will race against the clock to complete four gruelling cycle stages for charity.David Hunter, Derek Forsyth, and Graham Cunning, from Camp-bell Dallas LLP, are taking on the hills and islands of Argyll, North Kintyre and the Firth of Clyde, for the Prince and Princess of Wales Hospice.They will cycle the 52 miles of the Five Ferries Challenge on Wednesday. 